cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

The paper proposes a convolutional neural pyramid framework for low-level vision and image processing tasks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the efficiency and adaptivity of the proposed method, which are related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of neural networks also suggests the possibility of exploring neural engineering (cs.NE). Finally, the broad set of applications mentioned in the abstract, such as image filtering and colorization, may also relate to multimedia (cs.MM).
